\section*{Introduction}
The year is 1614. The Globe Theatre has been newly rebuilt after the devastating fire. However, a dire situation has arisen: Richard Burbage and the rest of the principal troupe have suddenly fallen ill. It falls to you, the second and third-rate actors, to perform the matinee of what might be the most crucial play in history. There's just one major problem—Shakespeare has been on a four-month bender, and the script is nowhere to be found. You'll need to improvise the entire performance. Use whatever resources you can muster, pull in people from the streets to act if necessary, and if it comes to it, even consider the scandalous act of casting women in the roles. The show must go on, no matter what.

